        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <figure id="f02901" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g02901.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. View of Extension Clip and "P" Clip Installation, in the Engine Compartment, Driver's
                    Side, Shown with Harnesses Removed for Clarity
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STEEL TUBES FROM BRAKE MASTER CYLINDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. NUT AND BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BRAKE TUBE BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. EXTENSION CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>5 "P" CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. BOLT, WASHER, AND NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage or personal injury, park the vehicle on a level surface, set the
                        parking brake, chock the wheels and turn the engine off.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nut and bolt from the bracket located between the two steel brake tubes
                    (Figure 1, Item 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the "P" clip over the two rubber brake lines (Figure 1, Item 5).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the "P" clip to the extension clip with a bolt, washer and nut, finger tight, as
                    shown in Figure 1, Item 6.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the extension clip assembly (Figure 1, Item 4) to the existing stand off bracket
                    with a nut and bolt (Figure 1, Item 2 and Item 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the nut and bolt at the "P" clip and the bracket to 13 Nm (9.6 Lbf-ft).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
